  <h1>Privacy Policy for Hootva</h1>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>Hootva collects information you provide voluntarily (e.g., name, email, date of birth), content you create in the app (messages, posts, images), device and usage data (analytics, crash logs), and location data if enabled.</p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide, maintain, and improve app functionality</li>
    <li>Personalize content and recommendations</li>
    <li>Send account-related notifications or updates</li>
    <li>Ensure security, detect fraud, and comply with laws</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Sharing Information</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal data. Data may be shared with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Third-party service providers for hosting, analytics, or support</li>
    <li>Legal authorities if required</li>
    <li>Protecting our rights, users, or public safety</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>
  <p>Data is stored using standard security practices. We cannot guarantee absolute security but use industry-standard measures to protect it.</p>

  <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>You can request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data and revoke consent where applicable.</p>

  <h2>6. Childrenâ€™s Privacy</h2>
  <p>The app is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.</p>

  <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
  <p>We may use cookies or similar technologies for analytics and personalization.</p>

  <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>The app may link to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for their privacy practices.</p>

  <h2>9. Policy Updates</h2>
